Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in The Bahamas. The Bahamian authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus, including entry restrictions.
From 19 March foreign nationals who have travelled within the last 20 days from the UK or other parts of Europe will be prohibited entry. Only Bahamian nationals and residents, will be allowed to enter, but will be quarantined or placed under self-isolation. Travellers can expect disruption to flights and should contact their airlines, travel agents and tour operators.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
